{
  "doc_id": "33406",
  "text": "To study whether the upregulation of Ntf3 in the Sip1 mutant has any effect on the proportion of AP and BP, we overexpressed Ntf3 in the wild-type (WT) cortex. BPs are situated in the subventricular zone (SVZ) and are responsible for the vast expansion of UL neuronal production, though they have been shown to produce all layers of the cortex [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Gotz and Huttner, 2005; [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] Pinto et al., 2009; [CITATION_6] .",
